## UI & Design Rules

### Color System — use CSS variables from globals.css
```css
--background: #050a14
--surface: #0d1a2e
--surface-elevated: #102240
--border: #1a3a5c
--accent-blue: #0094ff
--accent-neon: #00d4ff
--text-primary: #e8f4ff
--text-secondary: #6b9ab8
--green: #00c97a
--red: #ff3b5c
```
Never hardcode hex colors inline. Always reference these variables.

### PnL Color Convention
- Positive PnL / Long button: `var(--green)` (#00c97a)
- Negative PnL / Short button: `var(--red)` (#ff3b5c)
- Apply via Tailwind custom classes or inline CSS variables. Never use Tailwind's
  default `text-green-500` or `text-red-500` — they don't match the trading theme.

### shadcn/ui
- Use shadcn/ui components as the base for all UI elements (Button, Card, Dialog,
  Slider, Input, Table, Tabs, Badge).
- Customize via CSS variables, not by modifying shadcn source files directly.

### lightweight-charts
- The charting library is `lightweight-charts`. No other chart libraries for the
  price chart. Use `createChart` from the library.
- Always clean up the chart instance on component unmount to prevent memory leaks.
- Historical data for the chart comes from Binance Klines API, fetched client-side.

### Leverage Slider
- Range: 1x to 20x. Step: 1. Default: 5x.
- Always display the calculated Required Margin below the slider in real time.

