## TypeScript Rules

- Strict mode must remain enabled (`"strict": true` in tsconfig).
- No `any` types. Use `unknown` and narrow with type guards if needed.
- Define all database/domain types in `/lib/types.ts` and import from there.
- All Server Actions must be explicitly typed with their return value.
- The `position` object must always be typed as the full `Position` interface from
  `/lib/types.ts` — never use ad-hoc inline types for DB records.

